<p>Short question: <strong>WHY?!?</strong></p>  <p>The below class returns <em>ALL ALLRIGHT</em> when calling:<code>Status::validate('ab')</code></p>  <pre><code>class Status {     const FRESH = 0;     const PENDING = 25;     const CANCELLED = 50;      public static function validate($status)     {         switch ($status) {             case self::FRESH:             case self::PENDING:             case self::CANCELLED:                 echo 'ALL ALLRIGHT';             default:                 echo 'ERROR!';         }         die;     } } </code></pre>